6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to easements; enacting the Oklahoma
Uniform Easement Relocation Act of 2025; defining
8 terms; provides applicability of act to certain
easements; excludes certain easements from relation;
9 establishes the right of a property owner to relocate
an easement in certain circumstances; provides that a
10 property owner may commence a civil action to
relocate an easement; provides the requirements for
11 commencing a civil action to relocate an easement;
provides the court guidelines in creating an order
12 for relocation of an easement; requiring the
recordation of certain documents prior to relocation
13 of an easement; providing for reasonable expenses
related to the relocation of an easement; requires
14 the parties to a civil action for easement relocation
to act in good faith in facilitating relocation;
15 provides when a proposed easement relocation is
considered to be final and complete; provides and
16 limits the effect of an easement relocation; provides
that the right of a property to relocate an easement
17 under this act cannot be waived, excluded, or
restricted by agreement; provides that the law should
18 be applied and construed to promote uniformity with
other states that enact the act; provides relation to
19 the Electronic Signatures in Global and National
Commerce Act; provides that the act applies to an
20 easement created before, on, or after the effective
date of this bill; provides for codification; and
21 provides an effective date.
